:Dσ = dσ − A[σ]
and is the orthogonal form for .
What is the Hamiltonian version of this model? Well, first, we have to split A noncovariantly into a time component and a spatial part . Then, the resulting symplectic space has the conjugate variables , (taking values in the underlying vector space of formula_25, the dual rep of ), , &quot;A&quot;, &quot;φ&quot; and &quot;πφ&quot;. For each spatial point, we have the constraints, &quot;πφ&quot;=0 and the Gaussian constraint
:formula_26
where since is an intertwiner
