<doc id="880182" wikidata="Q16842719" url="?curid=880182" title="Black gang (ship)">
<text>The black gang are the members of a ship&#x27;s crew who work in the fire room/engine room; they are also called stokers or firemen. They are called &quot;black&quot; because of the soot and coal dust that is thick in the air in the fire room/engine room. The term began being used in the days of coal-fired steamships. The term is commonly used in the United States Coast Guard and United States Navy to describe personnel in &quot;M&quot; and &quot;B&quot; divisions.

