The equation of the envelope is then
:formula_8

Often when &quot;F&quot; is not a rational function of the parameter it may be reduced to this case by an appropriate substitution. For example, if the family is given by &quot;C&quot;θ with an equation of the form &quot;u&quot;(&quot;x&quot;, &quot;y&quot;)cos θ+&quot;v&quot;(&quot;x&quot;, &quot;y&quot;)sin θ=&quot;w&quot;(&quot;x&quot;, &quot;y&quot;), then putting &quot;t&quot;=&quot;e&quot;&quot;i&quot;θ, cos θ=(&quot;t&quot;+1/&quot;t&quot;)/2, sin θ=(&quot;t&quot;-1/&quot;t&quot;)/2&quot;i&quot; changes the equation of the curve to
